    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 10-12 min, turning occasionally until golden, crispy and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-and-mango-noodle-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chicken is cooking, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>red\u00a0chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop \ufb01nely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-and-mango-noodle-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fine egg noodles</strong> to a large bowl, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> until fully submerged and stir for 10 sec until the noodles separate</p><p>Set aside to soak for 4 min, or until softened</p><p>Once softened, drain the noodles, run them under <strong>cold water</strong> for 10 sec until slightly cooled, then set aside to\u00a0drain further</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-and-mango-noodle-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the noodles are softening, combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>rice vinegar</strong>\u00a0and\u00a0<strong>soy sauce</strong> with 3 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-and-mango-noodle-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>outer</strong> <strong>lettuce leaves </strong>into rough, bite-sized pieces and shred the<strong> inner core</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stalks and chop them roughly, discarding the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-and-mango-noodle-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and peel your<strong>\u00a0mango[es]</strong></p><p>Stand the\u00a0<strong>mango[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>upright and very carefully slice the flesh away from the <strong>stone[s]</strong></p><p>Tip: If you feel resistance against your knife, it means you are hitting the stone</p><p>Chop\u00a0the\u00a0<strong>mango\u00a0flesh</strong> into small bite-sized pieces, discarding the stone[s]</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-and-mango-noodle-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> torn lettuce</strong>, <strong>drained noodles</strong>, <strong>chopped mango</strong> and most of the\u00a0<strong>chopped chilli</strong>\u00a0(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)\u00a0to a large bowl with the <strong>dressing</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>noodle salad</strong></p><p>Transfer the<strong>\u00a0crispy chicken</strong> to a clean board and shred apart into roughly bite-sized pieces using two forks \u2013 this technique is known as 'pulling'</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chicken-and-mango-noodle-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>noodle salad</strong> topped with the <strong>crispy chicken</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped herbs</strong> and <strong>remaining chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
